\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 100 Seaview Terrace, Jppa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What year were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh now - forty - three from forty - '33, 1933.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Which year were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 1895.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Whereabouts were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Musselburgh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you give me the address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. 133 Inveresk Road, Musselburgh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh half a minute, it's thirty - 'til I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Until 1933?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have any brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Six brothers. I was the youngest of six. Five brothers and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How many years was there between each of them roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Could you give me their names and approximate birth date?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, I - I give you Ramsay. Alec first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Alec was the oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Ramsay. Andrew. John. James and myself. Now there would be a year and a half - to two years - between each - each one of us, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Have you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When I was born? Oh my goodness me
, now he was fifty-nine in 1930. Half a minute and I'll tell you. Thirteen and five's eighteen, eighteen off fifty-nine - forty-eighteen off of - eighteen off fifty-nine. Forty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - now I think he was Musselburgh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Builders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was he the owner of the firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, he - he was - a firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did he have any other jobs before he was a builder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no. Always a builder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did he have any other casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. That's my father you're - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How old would your mother be when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - I can't tell you but I can tell you she was - going on ninety-one when she died. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What year did she die, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh year, now - I would just guess - what year was it - I've got a note of it too. Half a minute, she was ninety-one. One from two's one - nine from seventeen leaves eight. Taking the ninety-one from 197
2. YES. Oh well, one from two leaves one, the - nine from seventeen is eight, 1881. 1881. 1881 and she was ninety - she was going on ninety-one now and it's seventeen - or eighteen - nineteen - 1971. Yes, yes. She'd be twenty-four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 She must have been married young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, she was married young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 East - Macmerry I think it was, Macmerry, East Lothian. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she ever work before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. She - she worked in the confectioner trade, she was a MacKintosh. And she helped her brothers in the confectioners trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 That was making sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Sweets, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she ever work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no, oh now, she had six in a family. That's a job. She worked, by God she worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember how many rooms there were in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 One, two, three, four - one - two, three four - four or - five, I would say five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What would you call these rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 There were three bedrooms. And there were - what they called the parlour then. And a - a sort of - kitchenette - you - dining rooms.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You ate in this room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You never had lodgers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Never, no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Very seldom. We used to help. The family used to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she ever have anybody to come in and do the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Or clean the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 She would do the washing herself at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were the clothes new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, the clothes were made - or mended by - a friend of my - mothe
r's who was a dress - you know, a dressmaker sort of thing. She used to do it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your mother ever buy second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I don't think so. But - we wore each other's clothes as we got up. You know, they were handed down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 If you were needing anything new did you get it at any time of the year or was there any special time when you got new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no special time at all. No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember where you got shoes from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - a Musselburgh shop, Millers - 
Millers shop in Musselburgh, shoe shop. That's the name, Millers shoe shop in Musselburgh, in the High Street there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 None whatever. Never - never did a thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Repairs or decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You said that you and your brothers helped in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What sort of jobs did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 All kinds of jobs. Cleaning and - you know, different jobs and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have any regular job that was yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. None whatever. No, we all just - we all just helped, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did the older ones help the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes, definitely. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember in your schooldays, were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember what time it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Half past seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember what age you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - half a minute now, I'll tell you. Ten or eight and - ten, I would say nine to ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, my brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have a bed each or did you share a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Shared the bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Which brother was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 James. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How did the rest of the family sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
They shared their beds too. And - the last two brothers - the eldest one, he - he died, he was skating, you know, sliding on - the ice at Muston Hall and he fell and - banged his head, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was that when he was quite young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 About sixteen. And he took concussion and he died. And Ramsay, he died when he was say nine or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You said that you ate in this kitchenette?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was there any occasion when you ate in the parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, when the friends came along. Yes, when there was a party or anything else. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What did your mother have to cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Now, the fire. No - no - no gas stove or anything else, just ordinary range. Just a range, yes. It - it was - it was an -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did it have an oven at the side of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Yes, an oven at the side of it, I remember it quite well. It was one of the old fashioned kind you know, the oven at the side and - yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember when you had breakfast, when you were a small child, was the whole family there together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Yes, practically. Yes. We'd all breakfast together, there was nonsense about it, we had to. Else we didn't get it. I would say - eight o'clock anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What would you usually have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 With sugar or salt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Porridge, no - no - not - no sugar, salt. YES. YES? YES.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What else would you have, toast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, just bread. Yes. Or sometimes rolls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have your lunch at home lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What would you have to eat then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Soup, always soup, broth or - mostly - always vegetable soup and - a meat course. And that's about - very seldom sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How often would you have meat in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh let me see. Saturday and Sunday - Sundays firs
tly we had. Monday now, Tuesday - let's say twice or thrice, three times, three - three times a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have tea in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Tea. Tea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What sort of tea would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Just a - ordinary tea with - mother's baking, scones or anything else or cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have a cooked meal then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have anything else before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. Sometimes we had porridge at night before we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. Don't remember her doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What about making jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes, she made all her jams, and all the rest of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she ever bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes. Not - not vegetables. Fruit, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she ever make wine or any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. Don't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did they grow fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, they grew vegetables and - mostly vegetables, and fruit, they had fruit too, they had fruit trees there too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 If they weren't in season did your mother still buy vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have any hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes. Hens and ducks. Yes, yes. Yes. And turkeys too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When meat was short at this time some people got some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you ever get that as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, my father used to go out with a gun. And he used to shoot and he used to go fishing too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862 Whereabouts would he go shoo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 ting?
