\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 YES.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did they ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 My father didn't read, my mother read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Your father didn't enjoy reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no, he didn't, he had too much - he had too much on his plate sort of - no, no. He wasn't a reader at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your mother ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When you were a young child do you ever remember funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 A funeral of my - yes, my - Alec I - my uncle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember at that time who attended the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Yes, my father - that's my - was my father's brother, you know, he was the painters in Musselburgh, Aitken and White, and - and my Uncle Jim,
 he was a - one of the MacKintoshs', the confectioners you see, came through - went through to his funeral, the whole crowd of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was it only the men that went to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes. And - mother too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 She went as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she go to the graveside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh no, no, no, just the house. The house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you wear mourning clothes at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Now I don't - now, we had - we had - we wore black you know, black ties and that. The usual, yes, usual ties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have armbands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Armbands? Yes, oh that's right, we had - armbands round - round our - sleeve there. Yes, that's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was it a walking funeral or did they have a hearse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Walking. Walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did friends attend as well or just family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh friends. Friends, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When you were young were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Very seldom. Very seldom I would say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Would it be your mother who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Mother would take us out. Like - might to - to her brother's or - them, but that's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, very very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you taken shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. Oh no, no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember any particular outings with your parents, such as on a Bank Holiday or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh - the - holiday - I - I remember most was - MacKintosh's usually had a - an outing for the employees and - mother and them were always invited to that outing. Now whether they either went t
o Peebles or somewhere - you know was - down to the border somewhere. Oh always looked forward to that every year. That was the outing we looked forward to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you go by train on these outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862 no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
. One of these - horse drawn wagonette things
, you know, the two horses and - sometimes four horses in. Oh yes. That was all. Yes. And - and of course we had then - the outings, but they - they weren't outings at all, the - the church outing. No, church outings wasn't - that wasn't an outing at all,
 that was - you know, your Bible classes and - all the rest of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. Never had a holiday. 'Til I was after I was married. No. We couldn't afford it, we hadn't - we hadn't the money enough.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Could you tell me how you spent a Saturday in these days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh, Saturday - in - in the summertime was always sport. Cricket or - football. Always. All my brothers all played and that. Yes. Were connected with boys teams and all - all the way through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What about the wintertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh wintertime we had the same sports, we had football in the wintertime. But cricket and that in the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What did you do on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh, Sunday, we had church in the morning, every one of us. Come on, dress and - all m
arched up like you were going like soldiers, they were all in a row right to the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Which church was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Inveresk Parish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 That's Church of Scotland is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Church of Scotland. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have different clothes to wear on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 YES. Yes. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Your parents thought it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 And you wasn't allowed to read - read any newspaper or anything else on Sunday. I suppose a Sunday was a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No working either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Your parents went to church themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you go once a day or did you go at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Sometimes at night. Then we had - at night we would - if we didn't go there, my brothers 
were at - what do you call it - the Bible Class. And I - the youngers ones, Jimmy and Jock, we went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was that in the afternoon, the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, the Sunday school was after the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were there any other social activities organised by the church that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh yes, there's - you had - they had - activities - that is for the elder - my brothers, Andrew and - and Jock, it was for the - now they had some - something at a night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 time - Bible Calls, they had some plays you know got up. Things like that. I can't remember that - at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember doing anything yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. We had nothing like that. Just the Bible Class you know. And - I've seen us having an outing you know, the crowd of
 us going away one day to - Peebles or - or Galashiels, there and back, that's all. - Summertime, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Would you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did the church run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were there any other clubs organised by the church that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. Not organised by the church, there were other clubs you went to but not by the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What sort of clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Physical Culture. And went to all - all these - physical culture classes. I did anyway, and Jimmy an
d that. And we had that all - practically all the year round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was that in a hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 In a hall, in the school, the old school we would be allowed permission in the gym and that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was your father interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. They were great - Tory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Why do you think he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Ah well, he had - he had always 
difficulty with labour. He had unemployed labour you see. And - he didn't like the outlook, or - or - the vie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
s of the Liberals at all. And that - that was the reason he stuck to - his Conservative - being a Conservative. And he was very much so a Conservative, he used to be - what do you call it, agents or anything you know what I mean - at election times.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 He actually belonged to the Conservative party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. He did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was your mother interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she ever vote at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. She always voted. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did she follow your father in her voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh I suppose she would, I think so. No, she had no independent views at all, not mother, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you think your father felt under any kind of pressure at his work to vote Tory at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I don't think so. Don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did he take part in any political activities other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, just election times. Municipal elections say, and - and - the Government. Bu
t - not - not outside that. Not to the meetings or anything like that. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When your parents weren't working how did they spend their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Well, my mother, she - she had - she was always working, she - she'd never any spare time. Espec
ially the whole lot of us to look after. Clothes and every blinking thing you know. And - well my father spent his spare time in yard I think it was. Just went on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did - they ever go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. Never - I never remember it. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Your mother wasn't interested in anything outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember when your father used to get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 About - six o'clock. Be about six o'clock but he was - the one thing a
bout him he was - he was too kind hearted to a lot of men and - you know, what I mean, he had to stand his hand and all the rest of it, sometimes it was six and seven. But he usually got a telling off when he came home. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your father take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no. Well he used to watch us at football. When we played football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did he ever go to the races at Musselburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. He - oh yes, he was on the committee of the Musselburgh - Racing Committee for these trotting ponies 
and all the rest of it. And he had these - ponies he had, or the horses he had was to run you know, at the local races.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did he ever bet on any of the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No, we weren't allowed to bet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your father and mother belong to any savings clubs that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How did you get on with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh very well, a hundred percent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was there any one that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Everyone of them was close. We were all - we're all for each other, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 As a child who did you used to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
With my brother, the one - older than myself, my - yes, my brother. And the school - I mean - before I want to school? School age? Oh well there were a lot of boys round - where we stayed you see, about the same age as myself, we used to play out and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Whereabouts did you usually play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh just in the streets or the back garden or any place we could. We played football or any of these games or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What other sort of games did you play as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
What you call rounders or something, you know, and - rounders and - what else now? That's all, I remember - I remember the rounders and remember the cricket and remember the football. That - that - I would say that was the two - t
he - the rounders and - most important ones, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Nobody minded?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I - I - could please myself who I played with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your parents ever discourage you from playing with a certain child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. My - we had - youth organisations, it was only starting then. And we were there for a very short time.
 Very short time. That was - we can say - we took a great part in the youth organisations at all. No. We - we were more - with the church. All the organisations in connection with the - under this - church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you belong to the Boys Brigade or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 My brothers were. I wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
When you were at school, how did you usually spend your free time other than just playing in the street, did you have any hobbies or keep pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - now, mostly games, football or - and 
doing your lessons. And - hobbies - that was the only thing, football or - or - or - cricket or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 For walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 We used to go shooting, you know, when we had a gun at the back where we used to have a 
target up you know. Shooting. That - that was - forgot about that. We had that in the back, but that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes. Yes. We couldn't afford bicycles. Walks, yes. Yes. But we were working then. We were carrying milk and - we were working and we -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have a milk round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. I - I had a milk round and - and we - we - had other messages to do for my brothers now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You didn't have all that much time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, and then that money all went into the home, it -
 see, I - I don't remember anything of it anyway but - it was always - you know, we were - Allens Dairy and - and Temples, that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How did you get this milk round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 By the lady when I - used to go for mother's milk, she said, hey, I want you
. Some hadn't turned up and I'd come out in the morning, I had to go out in the morning and back at night. And deliver milk.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember the hours that you had to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - it was early in the morning, about half past seven o'clock or so 
in the morning I would say. And - five to - no, it would be four to half past - half past four to about six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have to work Saturdays and Sundays as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Saturdays, Saturday and Sunday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember what you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - I - I don't think we received as much as - we didn't get two shillings a week, no, it was only a few - coppers we got paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 And you gave it all to mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Mother got it all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you ever have any other kind of jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No.
 I had that - later on. When I was at school, yes. Oh when I was at school I had my - that - when I was - ten I was working too. For my - father's books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 He paid you for that did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh no. No. You had to do it, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When you were a child did you go to any theatres, concerts, music halls or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - probably the only thing would be I - a concert, no - no music halls or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 A cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. Our cinema was the silent pictures. That was - oh that was once in a lifetime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have any pocket money when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Very little. I - I don't remember having any pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Not regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did anyone outside of the home help your mother look after h
er house or family, did she ever have relations or friends or neighbours coming in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh very seldom. A Miss Timm used to come round but very seldom. Very very seldom. She used to come round and - she - that's a dressmaker - lady, you know, she used to do - patching and - so - but that's the only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 If your mother was ill how did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Some of us would do it. Aye, yes, Jock or Jimmy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes. My - my - mother had her two bro
thers. Two - James MacKintosh and MacKintosh of Edinburgh, and my father had - Aitken the painters and a cousin at - Brewick Heath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you see much of your relations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh no. But I saw a lot of my - two - my three uncles, I saw quite a lot of them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you go to visit them or did they come to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh, we went to them and they came to us. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Friends? Oh yes, I would - say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Whereabouts did they usually see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - usually the friends was this dressmaker lady and - Arthur Oates - architect fellow came round to see father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 They came to see your parents did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Aye, they came - we never - we never visited them at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your mother and father share their friends or did your mother have friends and your father have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Well I think they all shared their friends as they came along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 And they were invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When they came were they offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Drinks mostly. YES. Never by mother of course, it was always father, because mother was very very - absolutely very bitter against - drink and smoking. She was - she - the one thing that she - she was very bitter against and 
she didn't allow it in the house at all, but - father was different when his friends came around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did these friends have to be invited or did they just drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh just drop in. Just drop in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did neighbours ever just drop in or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - sometimes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Very seldom. Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 If your father's friends came in for instance what would they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh they - they have - they had dominoes, cards and - what was that other thing they had - games you know, games they played at. They played games, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Many people divide society into different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 In the time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one class and some - another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What classes would you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I would call the upper class and the lower class. Two main classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How would you distinguish between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
The ones in the upper class was - the - people - say - compared with Lord Elphinstone, Sir Bertrand Milne and all these people. That was called the upper class. The lower class was business people and all the rest, all the o
ther people followed on. Only the two classes. Then that was - you know, what they called in these days was the gentry. They - they were the upper class.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 And everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 The lower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 So you would class yourself as being in the lower class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Lower class. But we didn't class ourself along in the same standing as Elphinston-s or Milnes or any of these people at all. And we always respected them as so. Nowadays they don't. No. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you ever told to touch your cap or call somebody sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What sort of people would you have to touch your hat to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Well I'd say the school - teachers, the ministers, doctors and all those - all your seniors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you ever remember anyone showing respect to your parents in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Showed - yes, showed - oh yes, all the boys - even the boys at our school, we were taught at school to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 In the district of Musselburgh who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 The Elphinstones. Lord Elphinstone. And Sir John Hope of Pinkie. And Sir Berkley Milne. That was about the three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Why were they particularly important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Wel
l, they - they had - they always held a high office, Sir Berkley Milne was something to do with the Navy, he was, you know, in charge. And - Sir John - Sir Alexander Hope, he - he was bland old man and he wanted so - he - he had a great big - wealth of - 
c
ountryside round about him and Elphinstone had the great Carberry Twoers. And - that's one, two three. That was the Church of Scotland now. Aye. That's - that's the three we looked at in Musselburgh. Elphinestone - Milne and - Sir John - and - and - Sir A
lexander Hope.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What about shopkeepers, were they important people or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, they were important people, in a sense but not - not in the same standing as - as the three I mentioned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did they just associate with other shopkeepers or did they associate with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
They had what they called the Merchants Association. They had - all - that - that was just their crowd you know, the Merchants Association, you had to belong to this association and that's all the shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 So they all tended to stick together did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Stick together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How about people such as ministers, teachers and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes - today - we got on well with them, the - the teachers very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did they mix with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes. Our -
 our ministers did. The teacher - although he did give you a little hander at times, he - he always - mixed with them all, yes, they do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What about farmers and employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes. The - no, the farmers and - and employers didn't mix so much as what they're doing now. They kept theirself a wee bit aloof.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What sort of people would you say went to the church at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - all sorts of people. A real mixture. All kinds. You - you - you had your attendanc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 , you had your church - churche
s pride. You - you had - you had a different - a different atmosphere altogether. I don't know what it was, but - you were brought up in this faith, and the children, and - and the boys and the whole lot was - you know - I - I remember Inveresk being pack
ed. You could hardly get in the seat on a Sunday. When the James Sharpe - that was the - Reverend James Sharpe was there. And he was looked at as one of the main - persons in the town. And - Inveresk Parish church. But oh now - good Lord, an awful change.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Where you lived did all the people in the lower class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups within the lower class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Different groups within the lower class, yes. You had the employers and the employees. That was the two different groups.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you think one group felt itself superior to the others or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 A little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were some families thought of as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Some families rough? How do you mean rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 In their way of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
In their way of living, oh yes, yes, yes, oh yes. Yes. Oh definitely - some family, you - you - you termed and you - you knew they were rough. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember if there was a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes. Definite distinction. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No. Mother had the same attitude to them all which made them all alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 She was just one of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 One, yes, one yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was it possible at that time to move from the lower class to the upper class or from the upper class to the lower class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 It was possible t
o move from the lower class to the upper class - more so than it was from the lower class - from the upper class to the lower class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was that because they need money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 They need money. That's right. It was money that came into that. Now, you - yo
u're coming into stages now - where money is - means an awful lot to the people. You know what I mean? Before, when you start, money was nothing at all. But now - you're coming in for the people are all - they're growing up, they want more money, they wan
t this, they want that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes, they were all - a lot of them described as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Why do you think they were called that, what was it that made them a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
There were Lady Elphinstone - am - am - am I going on Lady Elphinstone, because she did a lot of social work for them. We had - other - Doctor Scott's - wife, she did a lot of social work, you know, amongst the poor people. And Doctor Sc
ott did a lot of work amongst - and then a lot of social - helped other - others. That's what we exampled, of ladies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you ever remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 A policeman? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What did you think of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Frightened to death of them. Frightened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What do you think made you frightened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
What you'd been told about them. To keep out of their hands, out - away from the police altogether, send for a policeman, you know, if you did anything wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You were sometimes told that were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How do you think he actually treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 The policeman? Oh very well. They - they - they treated them all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 There really wasn't anything to be afraid of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 There was nothing to be afraid of, yes. But - it was just how you were told as you went along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was your home in Inveresk rented or did it belong to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 It belonged to my father, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you ever remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What difference did it make to the family if your father was ill or out of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 He was never out of work, but if he was ill did it make any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No, it didn't make so much diff
erence because - he - he - the - the business was still going on you see. But - where his business was - he had to pay two pounds a week I remember - plainly that he had to pay two pound a week to his step-father, out of the business. He kept on paying th
i
s two pound a week, and - and - he was to get the business. Well when his step-father died - he left it to his - daughter. And he had to pay out the business again, and that was just - sort of - you know - very - very difficult. It came very difficult for
 the whole family. But - thank goodness, we were - getting on. You know, what I mean, we were - growing up by that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 So you didn't ever have to get any help from anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember if there was ever anybody in the distr
ict whom the people disapproved of very strongly, was anyone ever chased out of their home or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, I don't - no, I don't think so. No - not - not in Inveresk. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents or did you go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh school yes. Yes. Oh yes. Oh I went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How old would you be when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 To work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 At school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How old? Four and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What time did you go in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When did you get back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh - I - now - I don't know when I got back, when I was only - young, but it used to be four in the afternoon. Four to half past four in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you think when you first started you'd only go in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Only mornings I think. No, I think I went the whole day. I'm sure I went the whole day. Straight from the beginning, right through.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you come home at lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Lunchtime and back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Newbigging. It was an ordinary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was it a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 A boarding? Board school, yes. Just for - you know - all the local children, yes. All them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Mixed school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh about - twenty minutes - half an hour - no - twenty minutes. Quarter of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Who usually went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Just your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Brothers. Brothers were always in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Liked it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Liked them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners, tidiness, punctuality and ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Always. Very important. I'll tell yo
u one thing that I objected - I was taken from that school and put to another school. And that - the only regret I had because I enjoyed the rough and ready school very much. Went to the grammar school. And you know, it set me back altogether because I lo
st all my old friends. I would never -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Why do you think you changed to the grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Because my mother wanted - were getting on and the business was going and they wanted something better than going to a rough and ready school, sent me to the grammar school. Which was a big mistake in my part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was that school run by the Corporation at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes, they were both run by the Corporation, but you'd - you'd a small fee to pay in the grammar. You had nothing to pay in the ordi
nary Newbigging. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You liked the old school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes, that - that - that - that seemed to - set me back tremendously, I - breaking away from that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How old were you when you went to the Grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Twelve, I think it was round about twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 So you probably would have to leave the other school anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
I would have had to leave the other school later on you see. But - I - I regret very much - getting sent away from there to - without my friends all coming with me. Still
 there it was. Yes, and it - it - I - I didn't take to the other school so much as I took to the - the ordinary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was it further away from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh now, it was practically the same. The same, yes. But - I had all my old friends, rough and r
eady and, you know - the old, what they used to call the gang and all the rest, and - and - but by God they were were well mannered and - far better mannered than what they were at the other school there. Because - we had a master there who just let them,
 you know, and the teachers too. Taught good manners and everything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What was the usual method of punishment at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 On your hand?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 For the boys and the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What sort of things did you get punished for at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh talking or - not doing your work or your homework or anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you ever get punished for actually making mistakes in your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes. For careless mistakes. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was it the same at the grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh I don't - the Grammar school, - it was different altogether there, I - I didn't like there so much. They hadn't the same - discipline or anything else at the Grammar. No, no. Newbigging was far far - streets ahead of them. Though it
 was rough and ready but still - you - you got good manners - you got - the English and arithmetic knocked into you, that's the two subjects they tried to give you. All this sort of Latin and all the other sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were your parents interested in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did they ever visit the school or the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did they ask you what you'd been doing when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 At Newbigging the other children came from similar types of home as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What about the Grammar school, was there any difference there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
No, no, they came - they came just the similar, just the merchants boys, their - their - their fathers had all sent them to the Grammar school, because
 they - they - they had a little fee to pay. And they thought they were getting - a higher education you see. That - that's the whole -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did the teachers ever single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No, I can't say that
 in the ordinary way, no. No. No, we were all treated alike, and - and, you know, the - the - boys that didn't behave, well they get a jolly good \{ILLEGIBLE\} and they sort of behaved the next time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Any groups? Oh - you - you used to have - their gangs, you know, they're all pals you know. Friendly gangs, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were there ever any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I don't think so, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Fourteen and a half, going on fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Aye, if I'd been in the old school I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 But you were glad to leave the Grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. I was glad to leave it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you have any education after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. Night classes. Yes. Evening classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Was that in Musselburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Edinburgh. High school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 None whatever. But - other - yes. The - the only thing
 is, you - you go back since then, but - you see, we're talking away back - and early days there when the education was never thought on as it is at the present time. But your experience going through life is now - if I was going back to school, jolly ass
ure I'd be working harder, I'd be doing this and doing that, I would be - taking languages and taking every sort of - other thing. But - you never thought about that when you were there. No, at the time. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 But you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh yes, I would say - benefit an awful lot from - from - night school. Oh yes, definitely. You got commercial subjects and you got all sorts of - things there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When you left school what was your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You went straight into the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Bank, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What exactly did you have to do in the Bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Well - messages rather and - count copper you know and - carry bags about. At ten pound per annum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 That was your pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Ten pound, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How often did you get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Monthly. Yes, yes, a lot to take home with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How did you get your job, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes. I remember it was through the church. That's how I got it. David S Lunnon was the accountant in the Royal Bank - was one of the h
ead men in the Head Office of the church. And - he used to see the family all growing up you know in their own - he spoke to mother then. What's - he asked - if I was leaving school. She said, no. He says, would like to come - I - I could get him into the
 
Bank if he'd like to come. Well, I said, oh she said - that - of course that took mother away up to the sky. I went down myself to see Mr Lunnan. Went down to Leadenhall, I saw Mr Lunnam, oh yes, so that time I got a - apprentice form to fill in, I filled
 it in. They said, beautiful, start at once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember the hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Hours. Nine o'clock, always nine o'clock and - sometimes five at night. Worked on the Saturday too to two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 That was your half day was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 YES? YES. You worked to two o'clock there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you get holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you feel that you were getting a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I felt I was getting a good wage at that time. Yes. And the second year I got fifteen pounds. And the third year I got twent
y. Very progress, very progressive I tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 All. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I presume your employer would be the Bank Manager, how did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, I liked him very much, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You liked the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I liked it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 After you started in the bank what was the next step after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Army. Yes. The world war broke out. And my 
brother Andrew was in the Army, Jock was in the Army. And - I was - in the Army, and Jim was left to carry on the business. And they said - to - well, mother said I was ready to go so I - I went away to the Army too. So they had only him left at home. But
 - unfortunately took him too. So the four of us was all in the Army. And she had to carry on the business while we were away. And so - Jock and - Jock was wounded twice and - Andrew was gassed. I was gassed, and that. But we all came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 After you came home what did you do then, go back into the Bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Go back, but I stayed on a year in the Army. Because - I had a better job in the Army than what I had in the Bank. I was a Regimental Quartermaster Sergeant. And I had a good pay. And I could - se
nd home - you know, you get - you're left so much off your pay. Even when I was a private I left so much off my pay, my mother collected at the Post Office. And then - the - you got your pay and - she got this money there and I took on for the six year, a
n
d I thought, what's the use of me coming back to the bank. Ten, twenty, thirty. I got forty pound when I came back. And had to go to Leith. You know, go to Leith and back. And - and the only way I could get to Leith is - sometimes I got there on a bus and
 sometimes I got - the Inveresk paper}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
mill lorry which I met and - five o'clock at night and I jumped on it and got - a ride home. And walked home at night. Then I got off from there, Leith to Newhaven. I got -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you termed a bank clerk at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Aye, a bank clerk and then I - I was made accountant at Newhaven. Yes. And I was there for a bit and I got on very well there. And then I was promoted to Morningside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Round about what year would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh - now I - I can't just tell y
ou the year. But it was Morningside, I was only two years at Newhaven and Morningside. And then - wait a minute -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You left the Army at the end of 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 I'll tell you, just a minute. I have it somewhere, I - Leith - oh I - 1910, 1914, 19 - 1920 -
 1919, 1920 Leith. 1923 was - Newhaven. 1923 went to Morningside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You said you were promoted there, what was your job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Accountant. A till accountant. Yes. No, no, teller accountant. That's generally two jobs, there's not such a thing now, 
it's only teller. Yes. Doing the two jobs there, and then - went down to Leven Street in 19 - 22. And from there, the manager died, and - fortunately - I applied for the job, I don't know, I didn't think I would get it, I was too young, I was young as you
 
might - accountant. So - ooh, I think I'll go down and see the - the manager. Went down there to see the general manager and I said, oh - there was much fuss and - at last I got in to see him. He said, come in. And I sat down and he spoke a while. He said
, you're - you're an Army man? I said, yes. He says, what }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15884563\charrsid11028862 battalion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
 were you with? I said, the Seaforth Highlanders. Oh. I said, yes. He said, Jock Henderson? I said, yes, I said, Jock Henderson, yes. That's the old Colonel you see. A great friend of mine. 
We were getting on very well. And then - he said - my brother, he says, aye Andrew, he says, he worked with me. - I says, yes. He says, is that your brother? I says, yes. Oh, he says, I - so he says, oh you make an application. So I went and put - and nex
t
 thing I heard I got the job. And I was the youngest bank manager. And from there - I think I got about - there were one place, Musselburgh - branch I was - sent to three times. When Stanley Johnson - when - when - Charlie Bairfield died Stanley Johnson d
i
ed and Mickey Reid died, and I got Bill Kiern the job down there, I spoke to Bill Kiern. But they wouldn't increase my salary so I said I was better staying with my old friends at Leven Street. So that's the reason I stopped at Leven Street, and I retired
 from there. I stood for five years bank manager there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 When was it that you retired then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
19 - 1959. The year - the day before I retired my great - my brother who had been - worked with him all - you know, worked - I was with him - spoke to him
 in the morning and he dropped down dead in the afternoon. He was calling in the afternoon, and - the next thing I - I - I couldn't believe it. They told me that Jimmy had - dropped down dead near Market Raisen. So - that - that sort of - you know, really
 - I was the - the only one left then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What did you do after you left the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Farmers and General - no, I went to my brother's - business to carry on when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 What sort of business did he have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Builders. He had my father's busin
ess you see. Yes. Yes. He had - he had a - enormous business. He had the best business - I know round about the Lothians, that - he had - I forget how many men, hundreds. Very big business. Grand - grand business, and - I went to help - the nephew but the
 
nephew came in and - well - I told him - told his - his mother what - Jimmy wanted, he wanted the business sold. And I thought it was the best thing - to sell it when you could get the big price for it. And they could look back and he could go and finish 
h
is accountant. Oh no, he just carry on, and they went on and they bust up the whole thing. And - I was only there how long, three month, I said, I'm finished, I'm out. I couldn't be bothered with that so I went to - Mr Lindsay came, he said, what are you 
doing? I said, nothing. Oh, he said, you're coming down to the - what do they call it - the Farmers and General.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Had it just started then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 It just started. I said, right - oh, I said, I don't mind going down there. Oh, he says, what are you going
 to do? Well, I said, I don't know. I said, it's new to me but I'll have a shot at it anyway. I went down and started and - built it up, now it's - it's - Caledonian Building Society. We started that, think it was about - ten - oh ten to twelve thousand, 
now we're about - six hundred and seventy thousand now. After ten thousand six hundred and something. Took a lot of working. Lot of hard work in the beginning. My Jove it took some work, it did. Yes. Yes. But still there it's at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Would you ever have preferred another type of job or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 No. No, I - I enjoyed my work. I enjoyed it, doesn't matter what - I enjoyed the work in the bank very much, I was very fond of it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you actually called an apprentice or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Apprentice, yes. Apprentice and ledgers clerk. Accountant and teller. A teller and accountant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 So you had to serve a sort of apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Apprenticeship, and then you - you come into your ledger clerk. Then you go ledger clerk to your telling on the telling pe
ople. From the teller to your accountant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 None. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you feel that there was a division of interest among workers, some people say that in these days there was a 
great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel there was a great division among workers at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh yes, there were - there was a great division, the - the trade workers and the - what they call the craftsmen - were - c
onsidered superior to the other workers altogether, you know, they were important craftsmen. They'd served their apprenticeship and - and what they are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Full time work? I had full time work all my life so it never occurred to me - I started work at - when I was ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you think that once you left school your attitude changed at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 None whatever. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You continued to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you think that once you were working your relationship with your parents and your brothers changed any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 None whatever. We were more - helping each other. My brother helped me tremendously, and I helped his business tremendously. And
 Jock, we helped Jock and - and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Did you spend Sunday and differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 You stopped going to Sunday school presumably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Sunday - no Sunday school, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Would you go to Bible Class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Yes, sometimes we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you interested at all in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 
Oh - I went to meetings but that was all. Because - in - one - one of the rules in the bank was that we wouldn't - participate in any politics or anything like that. That'
s right. That was one - one of the rules, so I - I never - I used to obey the rules, I never - never took any - active part or anything else. I went to the meetings and hard - different meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Were you allowed to vote for anyone you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 O
h you vote, yes, aye, but you weren't allowed to take part, they thought it was - very bad for a bank manager - taking a part, because - you didn't know who you were - upsetting you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Even as an apprentice you weren't allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 And secrecy
 was another - you weren't allowed to divulge a thing and - all - all for ten pound a year. Twenty - twenty, thirty, forty, like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you remember voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8078847 GA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Oh, before 1919? Oh no, I don't - 1919, I was just c
oming back from the Army, I was in the Army - I was four years in the Army you see. No, I don't remember going to vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3934310 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16216466\charrsid11028862 Do you know if your wife ever voted in a general election at that time?
